  "about_bioName": "José Guilherme Alves",
  "about_bioTitle": "Mobile front end · Flutter Developer · Brazil",
  "about_bioParagraph": "Career started in retail mobile apps — Flutter front end from design to deploy, in a small team, over 5 years. Then moved to product teams across larger domains: public services, internal platforms, field operations, and currently fintech at scale. Always on the mobile front end, with Flutter web when the product demanded it. Constant focus on architecture, performance, and UX consistency on real devices.",

  "delivery_entrega_eyebrow": "DELIVERY",
  "delivery_entrega_title": "Clear scope,",
  "delivery_entrega_titleAccent": "aligned expectations.",
  "delivery_entrega_body": "Every project starts with the cut: what's in, what's out, and how each decision ties to an acceptance criterion. Without that, sprints become deadline races. I work with PO and design from kickoff so the backlog reflects what ships — not what looks good in the prototype.",
  "delivery_craft_eyebrow": "CRAFT",
  "delivery_craft_title": "Real architecture",
  "delivery_craft_titleAccent": "and performance.",
  "delivery_craft_body": "Clean Architecture per feature, Bloc/Cubit for state, CustomPainter when vectors are cheaper than assets. Measures frame time on real devices (not emulators), profiles build time, audits rebuilds. A production stack sustains evolution — it doesn't stall two months after the MVP.",
  "delivery_collab_eyebrow": "COLLABORATION",
  "delivery_collab_title": "On a product team",
  "delivery_collab_titleAccent": "or owning the entire Flutter side.",
  "delivery_collab_body": "On large teams I join as mobile front end with feature scope or architectural stewardship. On small teams (B2B retail, 5 years) I owned the entire Flutter side — from design to deploy, integrating existing APIs and helping shape new contracts when needed. I adapt to the team size, not the other way around.",

