  "caseStudy_eyebrow": "Case study",
  "caseStudy_title": "Pulso rewritten —",
  "caseStudy_titleAccent": "dark Whoop, from scratch.",
  "caseStudy_subtitle": "The fitness mock started cream/orange, Strava-style. It was pivoted to dark recovery-first inspired by Whoop after a critical review session of the closing scroll. Here are the decisions that sustain the new Pulso.",
  "caseStudy_pivotEyebrow": "THE PIVOT",
  "caseStudy_pivotTitle": "From lightweight logger to reading dashboard.",
  "caseStudy_pivotPara1": "The first version of Pulso was a common tracker: Today tab, Week tab, Progress tab. Everything worked — set dots, rings, volume — but the experience boiled down to \"seeing numbers\". Three out of four screens were read-only.",
  "caseStudy_pivotPara2": "The rewrite flipped the focus: recovery first, logger second. 8-week mesocycle with linear progression + deload on the last. Each logged set advances a strain accumulator that reacts in real time. The cream/orange palette gave way to recovery green #00D982 and strain cyan #5AC8FA on near-black surface — explicit Whoop reference, no pretense of originality.",
  "caseStudy_pivotPara3": "The domain grew: Program, ProgramWeek, SessionTemplate, PlannedExercise, SetEntry, LoggedSession, RecoverySnapshot, StrainScore, MuscleRecovery, SleepWindow. All plain Dart with Equatable — no freezed, no codegen — to keep the workspace free of build_runner.",
  "caseStudy_recoveryLabel": "PULSO · TODAY",
  "caseStudy_recoveryHint": "All green. Use the window for intense work\nfollowing the mesocycle pattern.",
  "caseStudy_painterStrainTitle": "Strain dial",
  "caseStudy_painterStrainCaption": "Whoop's 0–21 logarithmic scale. Arc with blue → magenta gradient. Centered monospace numeral for equipment-style readout.",
  "caseStudy_painterTempoTitle": "Tempo bars",
  "caseStudy_painterTempoCaption": "4 phases — eccentric / pause / concentric / pause — with a luminous cursor looping. Runs on AnimationController passed directly to CustomPainter via super(repaint:).",
  "caseStudy_painterPeriodTitle": "Periodization grid",
  "caseStudy_painterPeriodCaption": "8-week × 7-day mesocycle. Heat by prescribed intensity, border on current week, distinct deload coloring. Tap any cell to reveal the session.",
  "caseStudy_decisionArchEyebrow": "ARCHITECTURE",
  "caseStudy_decisionArchTitle": "Clean Arch per mock, not per package",
  "caseStudy_decisionArchBody": "Each showcase mock (Pulso, Garoa, Aurora, Vitral, Solar) has its own data / domain / presentation triangle inside lib/src/<mock>/. Mocks don't import each other — only shared/. When a mock grows in entities, everything fits inside its own triangle.",
  "caseStudy_decisionPaintersEyebrow": "PAINTERS",
  "caseStudy_decisionPaintersTitle": "super(repaint:) and strict shouldRepaint",
  "caseStudy_decisionPaintersBody": "Animated painters receive the AnimationController directly in super(repaint:) — the engine skips build/layout and goes straight to paint. shouldRepaint compares field by field. No allocation in the hot loop: Paint, Path and TextPainter cached as static fields of the painter.",
  "caseStudy_decisionStateEyebrow": "STATE",
  "caseStudy_decisionStateTitle": "Rich Bloc, set-by-set with RPE",
  "caseStudy_decisionStateBody": "The old state (completedSets[weekday|exerciseId] map) was replaced by LoggedSession with typed SetEntry: weight, reps, RPE, completed, notes. SetLogged moves the strain accumulator in real time — set becoming complete advances, becoming incomplete recedes. No freezed; Equatable gives us the == we need.",
  "caseStudy_takeawayEyebrow": "TAKEAWAY",
  "caseStudy_takeawayTitle": "Showcase mocks aren't palette demos — they're proof that the code survives a product pivot without becoming a hack.",
  "caseStudy_takeawayBody": "The Pulso pivot swapped ~5K LOC of UI while keeping the core → design_system → animations → feature_* hierarchy, no new dep, no regression on the rest of the scroll. The painters reuse everything that already existed in the sub-feature itself. The code you see above is running exactly as in the Pulso session — no mirror, no screenshot.",

